.TH "BSON_REINIT" "3" "2014-08-19" "libbson"
.SH NAME
bson_reinit()
.SH "SYNOPSIS"

.nf
.nf
void
bson_reinit (bson_t *b);
.fi
.fi

.SH "PARAMETERS"

.TP
.B b
A
.BR bson_t
\&.
.LP

.SH "DESCRIPTION"

The
.BR bson_reinit(3)
function shall be equivalent to calling
.BR bson_destroy(3)
and
.BR bson_init(3)
\&.

However, if the
.BR bson_t
structure contains a malloc()'d buffer, it may be reused.


